# Next.js 14+ App Router Standards

## File Structure

```
apps/website/src/
├── app/              # App Router pages and layouts
├── components/       # Reusable components
├── lib/             # Utility functions and API clients
├── hooks/           # Custom React hooks
├── types/           # TypeScript type definitions
└── styles/          # Global styles
```

## Page Components

- Use `'use client'` only when necessary (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)
- Prefer Server Components by default for better performance
- Keep page components focused on layout and data fetching
- Extract complex logic into separate components or hooks

## Layouts

- Use layouts for shared UI (navbar, sidebar, footer)
- Nest layouts for hierarchical page structures
- Keep layouts lightweight and focused on structure
- Avoid heavy computations in layouts

## Route Handlers

- Use `app/api/*` for API routes when needed
- Prefer backend API for database operations
- Use route handlers for third-party integrations
- Implement proper error handling and validation

