# Error Handling

## User-Facing Errors

- Arabic-first UX where the project already uses Arabic
- Use existing helpers for error mapping
- Never show raw backend keys or stack traces
- Provide clear, actionable error messages
- Offer retry actions when appropriate

## Error Boundaries

- Use error boundaries for route-level error handling
- Provide fallback UI for errors
- Log errors for debugging
- Implement recovery mechanisms

## API Error Handling

```typescript
try {
  const data = await fetchData();
} catch (error) {
  const message = getUserFacingErrorMessage(error);
  toast.error(message);
}
```

---

# Forms and Validation

## Form Libraries

- Use React Hook Form for complex forms
- Use Zod for schema validation
- Implement client-side validation
- Show clear field-level errors

## Form Patterns

- Disable submit buttons while submitting
- Preserve user input on validation errors
- Show progress indicators for long operations
- Implement optimistic UI when appropriate

## Validation

- Validate on blur for better UX
- Show errors immediately after submission
- Use consistent error messages
- Provide clear success feedback

---

# Accessibility (a11y)

## Semantic HTML

- Use proper HTML5 semantic elements
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Provide ARIA labels when needed
- Maintain proper heading hierarchy

## Screen Readers

- Use descriptive alt text for images
- Announce dynamic content changes
- Provide skip navigation links
- Ensure color contrast meets WCAG standards

## Focus Management

- Manage focus in modals and dialogs
- Provide visible focus indicators
- Handle focus trapping in overlays
- Restore focus after closing modals

---

# SEO and Meta Tags

## Next.js Metadata

- Use metadata API for page metadata
- Provide unique titles and descriptions
- Implement Open Graph tags
- Add structured data when appropriate

## Performance SEO

- Ensure fast page loads (< 3s)
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use semantic HTML for better indexing
- Optimize images and fonts

---

# Testing Standards

## Unit Tests

- Test components in isolation
- Mock external dependencies
- Test user interactions
- Cover edge cases

## Integration Tests

- Test page-level flows
- Test API integrations
- Test authentication flows
- Use Playwright for E2E tests

